 ### Helper Templates (_helpers.tpl)\n576: \n577: ```yaml\n578: {{/*\n579: Expand the name of the chart.\n580: */}}\n581: {{- define \"agentcube.name\" -}}\n582: {{- default .Chart.Name .Values.nameOverride | trunc 63 | trimSuffix \"-\" }}\n583: {{- end }}\n584: \n585: {{/*\n586: Create a default fully qualified app name.\n587: */}}\n588: {{- define \"agentcube.fullname\" -}}\n589: {{- if .Values.fullnameOverride }}\n590: {{- .Values.fullnameOverride | trunc 63 | trimSuffix \"-\" }}\n591: {{- else }}\n592: {{- $name := default .Chart.Name .Values.nameOverride }}\n593: {{- if contains $name .Release.Name }}\n594: {{- .Release.Name | trunc 63 | trimSuffix \"-\" }}\n595: {{- else }}\n596: {{- printf \"%s-%s\" .Release.Name $name | trunc 63 | trimSuffix \"-\" }}\n597: {{- end }}\n598: {{- end }}\n599: {{- end }}\n600: \n601: {{/*\n602: Create chart name and version as used by the chart label.\n603: */}}\n604: {{- define \"agentcube.chart\" -}}\n605: {{- printf \"%s-%s\" .Chart.Name .Chart.Version | replace \"+\" \"_\" | trunc 63 | trimSuffix \"-\" }}\n606: {{- end }}\n607: \n608: {{/*\n609: Common labels\n610: */}}\n611: {{- define \"agentcube.labels\" -}}\n612: helm.sh/chart: {{ include \"agentcube.chart\" . }}\n613: {{ include \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" . }}\n614: {{- if .Chart.AppVersion }}\n615: app.kubernetes.io/version: {{ .Chart.AppVersion | quote }}\n616: {{- end }}\n617: app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: {{ .Release.Service }}\n618: {{- end }}\n619: \n620: {{/*\n621: Selector labels\n622: */}}\n623: {{- define \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" -}}\n624: app.kubernetes.io/name: {{ include \"agentcube.name\" . }}\n625: app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}\n626: {{- end }}\n627: \n628: {{/*\n629: Create the name of the service account to use\n630: */}}\n631: {{- define \"agentcube.controllerManager.serviceAccountName\" -}}\n632: {{- if .Values.controllerManager.serviceAccount.create }}\n633: {{- default (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) .Values.controllerManager.serviceAccount.name }}\n634: {{- else }}\n635: {{- default \"default\" .Values.controllerManager.serviceAccount.name }}\n636: {{- end }}\n637: {{- end }}\n638: \n639: {{/*\n640: Create the name of the service account to use\n641: */}}\n642: {{- define \"agentcube.workloadManager.serviceAccountName\" -}}\n643: {{- if .Values.workloadManager.serviceAccount.create }}\n644: {{- default (printf \"%s-workload-manager\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .)) .Values.workloadManager.serviceAccount.name }}\n645: {{- else }}\n646: {{- default \"default\" .Values.workloadManager.serviceAccount.name }}\n647: {{- end }}\n648: {{- end }}\n649: \n650: {{/*\n651: Create the name of the service account to use\n652: */}}\n653: {{- define \"agentcube.router.serviceAccountName\" -}}\n654: {{- if .Values.router.serviceAccount.create }}\n655: {{- default (printf \"%s-router\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .)) .Values.router.serviceAccount.name }}\n656: {{- else }}\n657: {{- default \"default\" .Values.router.serviceAccount.name }}\n658: {{- end }}\n659: {{- end }}\n660: \n661: {{/*\n662: Image registry helper\n663: */}}\n664: {{- define \"agentcube.imageRegistry\" -}}\n665: {{- .Values.global.imageRegistry | default \"\" -}}\n666: {{- end }}\n667: \n668: {{/*\n669: Build fully qualified image reference\n670: */}}\n671: {{- define \"agentcube.image\" -}}\n672: {{- $registry := include \"agentcube.imageRegistry\" . -}}\n673: {{- if $registry }}\n674: {{- printf \"%s/%s:%s\" $registry .repository .tag }}\n675: {{- else }}\n676: {{- printf \"%s:%s\" .repository .tag }}\n677: {{- end }}\n678: {{- end }}\n679: ```\n680: \n681: ## API Contracts\n682: \n683: ### Template: CRD Installation\n684: \n685: **File:** `templates/crds/agentruntime.yaml`\n686: \n687: ```yaml\n688: {{- if .Values.controllerManager.enabled }}\n689: apiVersion: apiextensions.k8s.io/v1\n690: kind: CustomResourceDefinition\n691: metadata:\n692:   name: agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n693:   annotations:\n694:     helm.sh/hook: crd-install\n695:     helm.sh/hook-weight: \"-5\"\n696:     helm.sh/hook-delete-policy: before-hook-creation\n697:   labels:\n698:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n699: spec:\n700:   group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n701:   names:\n702:     kind: AgentRuntime\n703:     listKind: AgentRuntimeList\n704:     plural: agentruntimes\n705:     shortNames:\n706:     - art\n707:     singular: agentruntime\n708:   scope: Namespaced\n709:   versions:\n710:   - name: v1alpha1\n711:     served: true\n712:     storage: true\n713:     schema:\n714:       openAPIV3Schema:\n715:         type: object\n716:         properties:\n717:           apiVersion:\n718:             type: string\n719:           kind:\n720:             type: string\n721:           metadata:\n722:             type: object\n723:           spec:\n724:             type: object\n725:             properties:\n726:               maxSessionDuration:\n727:                 type: string\n728:                 default: \"8h\"\n729:               sessionTimeout:\n730:                 type: string\n731:                 default: \"15m\"\n732:               podTemplate:\n733:                 type: object\n734:                 properties:\n735:                   metadata:\n736:                     type: object\n737:                   spec:\n738:                     type: object\n739:               targetPort:\n740:                 type: array\n741:                 items:\n742:                   type: object\n743:                   properties:\n744:                     port:\n745:                       type: integer\n746:                       format: int32\n747:                     protocol:\n748:                       type: string\n749:                       enum: [\"HTTP\", \"HTTPS\"]\n750:                     pathPrefix:\n751:                       type: string\n752:                     name:\n753:                       type: string\n754:                 required: [\"port\", \"protocol\"]\n755:             required: [\"maxSessionDuration\", \"sessionTimeout\", \"podTemplate\", \"targetPort\"]\n756:           status:\n757:             type: object\n758:             properties:\n759:               conditions:\n760:                 type: array\n761:                 items:\n762:                   type: object\n763:                   properties:\n764:                     lastTransitionTime:\n765:                       format: date-time\n766:                       type: string\n767:                     message:\n768:                       type: string\n769:                     reason:\n770:                       type: string\n771:                     status:\n772:                       type: string\n773:                     type:\n774:                       type: string\n775:                     observedGeneration:\n776:                       format: int64\n777:                       type: integer\n778:               observedGeneration:\n779:                 format: int64\n780:                 type: integer\n781:     subresources:\n782:       status: {}\n783:     additionalPrinterColumns:\n784:     - name: Age\n785:       type: date\n786:       jsonPath: .metadata.creationTimestamp\n787: {{- end }}\n788: ```\n789: \n790: ### Template: Controller Manager Deployment\n791: \n792: **File:** `templates/controller-manager/deployment.yaml`\n793: \n794: ```yaml\n795: {{- if .Values.controllerManager.enabled }}\n796: apiVersion: apps/v1\n797: kind: Deployment\n798: metadata:\n799:   name: {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}\n800:   namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n801:   labels:\n802:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n803:     app.kubernetes.io/component: controller-manager\n804: spec:\n805:   replicas: {{ .Values.controllerManager.replicaCount }}\n806:   selector:\n807:     matchLabels:\n808:       {{- include \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" . | nindent 6 }}\n809:       app.kubernetes.io/component: controller-manager\n810:   template:\n811:     metadata:\n812:       annotations:\n813:         checksum/config: {{ include (print $.Template.BasePath \"/configmaps/config.yaml\") . | sha256sum }}\n814:         {{- with .Values.controllerManager.podAnnotations }}\n815:         {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n816:         {{- end }}\n817:       labels:\n818:         {{- include \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" . | nindent 8 }}\n819:         app.kubernetes.io/component: controller-manager\n820:         {{- with .Values.controllerManager.podLabels }}\n821:         {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n822:         {{- end }}\n823:     spec:\n824:       {{- with .Values.imagePullSecrets }}\n825:       imagePullSecrets:\n826:         {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n827:       {{- end }}\n828:       serviceAccountName: {{ include \"agentcube.controllerManager.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n829:       securityContext:\n830:         {{- toYaml .Values.controllerManager.securityContext | nindent 8 }}\n831:       {{- with .Values.controllerManager.nodeSelector }}\n832:       nodeSelector:\n833:         {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n834:       {{- end }}\n835:       {{- with .Values.controllerManager.affinity }}\n836:       affinity:\n837:         {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n838:       {{- end }}\n839:       {{- with .Values.controllerManager.tolerations }}\n840:       tolerations:\n841:         {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n842:       {{- end }}\n843:       {{- if .Values.priorityClassName }}\n844:       priorityClassName: {{ .Values.priorityClassName }}\n845:       {{- end }}\n846:       containers:\n847:       - name: controller-manager\n848:         securityContext:\n849:           {{- toYaml .Values.controllerManager.containerSecurityContext | nindent 10 }}\n850:         image: \"{{ include \"agentcube.image\" (dict \"registry\" .Values.global.imageRegistry \"repository\" .Values.controllerManager.image.repository \"tag\" .Values.controllerManager.image.tag) }}\"\n851:         imagePullPolicy: {{ .Values.controllerManager.image.pullPolicy }}\n852:         args:\n853:         - --leader-elect\n854:         - --health-probe-bind-address=:8080\n855:         - --metrics-bind-address=:9090\n856:         ports:\n857:         - name: http\n858:           containerPort: 8080\n859:           protocol: TCP\n860:         - name: metrics\n861:           containerPort: 9090\n862:           protocol: TCP\n863:         {{- with .Values.controllerManager.livenessProbe }}\n864:         livenessProbe:\n865:           {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n866:         {{- end }}\n867:         {{- with .Values.controllerManager.readinessProbe }}\n868:         readinessProbe:\n869:           {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n870:         {{- end }}\n871:         resources:\n872:           {{- toYaml .Values.controllerManager.resources | nindent 10 }}\n873:         {{- with .Values.controllerManager.env }}\n874:         env:\n875:           {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n876:         {{- end }}\n877:         {{- with .Values.controllerManager.envFrom }}\n878:         envFrom:\n879:           {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n880:         {{- end }}\n881:         {{- with .Values.controllerManager.extraVolumeMounts }}\n882:         volumeMounts:\n883:           {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n884:         {{- end }}\n885:       {{- with .Values.controllerManager.extraVolumes }}\n886:       volumes:\n887:         {{- toYaml . | nindent 6 }}\n888:       {{- end }}\n889: {{- end }}\n890: ```\n891: \n892: ### Template: Controller Manager Service\n893: \n894: **File:** `templates/controller-manager/service.yaml`\n895: \n896: ```yaml\n897: {{- if .Values.controllerManager.enabled }}\n898: apiVersion: v1\n899: kind: Service\n900: metadata:\n901:   name: {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}\n902:   namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n903:   labels:\n904:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n905:     app.kubernetes.io/component: controller-manager\n906:   {{- with .Values.controllerManager.service.annotations }}\n907:   annotations:\n908:     {{- toYaml . | nindent 4 }}\n909:   {{- end }}\n910: spec:\n911:   type: {{ .Values.controllerManager.service.type }}\n912:   ports:\n913:   - port: {{ .Values.controllerManager.service.port }}\n914:     targetPort: http\n915:     protocol: TCP\n916:     name: http\n917:   selector:\n918:     {{- include \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n919:     app.kubernetes.io/component: controller-manager\n920: {{- end }}\n921: ```\n922: \n923: ### Template: Controller Manager ServiceAccount\n924: \n925: **File:** `templates/controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml`\n926: \n927: ```yaml\n928: {{- if and .Values.controllerManager.enabled .Values.controllerManager.serviceAccount.create }}\n929: apiVersion: v1\n930: kind: ServiceAccount\n931: metadata:\n932:   name: {{ include \"agentcube.controllerManager.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n933:   namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n934:   labels:\n935:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n936:     app.kubernetes.io/component: controller-manager\n937:   {{- with .Values.controllerManager.serviceAccount.annotations }}\n938:   annotations:\n939:     {{- toYaml . | nindent 4 }}\n940:   {{- end }}\n941: {{- end }}\n942: ```\n943: \n944: ### Template: Controller Manager RBAC\n945: \n946: **File:** `templates/controller-manager/rbac.yaml`\n947: \n948: ```yaml\n949: {{- if and .Values.controllerManager.enabled .Values.controllerManager.rbac.create }}\n950: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n951: kind: Role\n952: metadata:\n953:   name: {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}\n954:   namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n955:   labels:\n956:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n957:     app.kubernetes.io/component: controller-manager\n958: rules:\n959: {{- toYaml .Values.controllerManager.rbac.rules | nindent 0 }}\n960: ---\n961: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n962: kind: RoleBinding\n963: metadata:\n964:   name: {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}\n965:   namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n966:   labels:\n967:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n968:     app.kubernetes.io/component: controller-manager\n969: roleRef:\n970:   apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n971:   kind: Role\n972:   name: {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}\n973: subjects:\n974: - kind: ServiceAccount\n975:   name: {{ include \"agentcube.controllerManager.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n976:   namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n977: {{- end }}\n978: ```\n979: \n980: ### Template: Workload Manager Deployment\n981: \n982: **File:** `templates/workload-manager/deployment.yaml`\n983: \n984: ```yaml\n985: {{- if .Values.workloadManager.enabled }}\n986: apiVersion: apps/v1\n987: kind: Deployment\n988: metadata:\n989:   name: {{ printf \"%s-workload-manager\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }}\n990:   namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n991:   labels:\n992:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n993:     app.kubernetes.io/component: workload-manager\n994: spec:\n995:   replicas: {{ .Values.workloadManager.replicaCount }}\n996:   selector:\n997:     matchLabels:\n998:       {{- include \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" . | nindent 6 }}\n999:       app.kubernetes.io/component: workload-manager\n1000:   template:\n1001:     metadata:\n1002:       annotations:\n1003:         checksum/config: {{ include (print $.Template.BasePath \"/configmaps/config.yaml\") . | sha256sum }}\n1004:         {{- with .Values.workloadManager.podAnnotations }}\n1005:         {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n1006:         {{- end }}\n1007:       labels:\n1008:         {{- include \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" . | nindent 8 }}\n1009:         app.kubernetes.io/component: workload-manager\n1010:         {{- with .Values.workloadManager.podLabels }}\n1011:         {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n1012:         {{- end }}\n1013:     spec:\n1014:       {{- with .Values.imagePullSecrets }}\n1015:       imagePullSecrets:\n1016:         {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n1017:       {{- end }}\n1018:       serviceAccountName: {{ include \"agentcube.workloadManager.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n1019:       securityContext:\n1020:         {{- toYaml .Values.workloadManager.securityContext | nindent 8 }}\n1021:       {{- with .Values.workloadManager.nodeSelector }}\n1022:       nodeSelector:\n1023:         {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n1024:       {{- end }}\n1025:       {{- with .Values.workloadManager.affinity }}\n1026:       affinity:\n1027:         {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n1028:       {{- end }}\n1029:       {{- with .Values.workloadManager.tolerations }}\n1030:       tolerations:\n1031:         {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n1032:       {{- end }}\n1033:       {{- if .Values.priorityClassName }}\n1034:       priorityClassName: {{ .Values.priorityClassName }}\n1035:       {{- end }}\n1036:       containers:\n1037:       - name: workload-manager\n1038:         securityContext:\n1039:           {{- toYaml .Values.workloadManager.containerSecurityContext | nindent 10 }}\n1040:         image: \"{{ include \"agentcube.image\" (dict \"registry\" .Values.global.imageRegistry \"repository\" .Values.workloadManager.image.repository \"tag\" .Values.workloadManager.image.tag) }}\"\n1041:         imagePullPolicy: {{ .Values.workloadManager.image.pullPolicy }}\n1042:         args:\n1043:         - --leader-elect\n1044:         - --health-probe-bind-address=:8080\n1045:         - --metrics-bind-address=:9090\n1046:         ports:\n1047:         - name: http\n1048:           containerPort: 8080\n1049:           protocol: TCP\n1050:         - name: metrics\n1051:           containerPort: 9090\n1052:           protocol: TCP\n1053:         {{- with .Values.workloadManager.livenessProbe }}\n1054:         livenessProbe:\n1055:           {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n1056:         {{- end }}\n1057:         {{- with .Values.workloadManager.readinessProbe }}\n1058:         readinessProbe:\n1059:           {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n1060:         {{- end }}\n1061:         resources:\n1062:           {{- toYaml .Values.workloadManager.resources | nindent 10 }}\n1063:         {{- with .Values.workloadManager.env }}\n1064:         env:\n1065:           {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n1066:         {{- end }}\n1067:         {{- with .Values.workloadManager.envFrom }}\n1068:         envFrom:\n1069:           {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n1070:         {{- end }}\n1071:         {{- with .Values.workloadManager.extraVolumeMounts }}\n1072:         volumeMounts:\n1073:           {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n1074:         {{- end }}\n1075:       {{- with .Values.workloadManager.extraVolumes }}\n1076:       volumes:\n1077:         {{- toYaml . | nindent 6 }}\n1078:       {{- end }}\n1079: {{- end }}\n1080: ```\n1081: \n1082: ### Template: Router Deployment\n1083: \n1084: **File:** `templates/router/deployment.yaml`\n1085: \n1086: ```yaml\n1087: {{- if .Values.router.enabled }}\n1088: apiVersion: apps/v1\n1089: kind: Deployment\n1090: metadata:\n1091:   name: {{ printf \"%s-router\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }}\n1092:   namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n1093:   labels:\n1094:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n1095:     app.kubernetes.io/component: router\n1096: spec:\n1097:   replicas: {{ .Values.router.replicaCount }}\n1098:   selector:\n1099:     matchLabels:\n1100:       {{- include \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" . | nindent 6 }}\n1101:       app.kubernetes.io/component: router\n1102:   template:\n1103:     metadata:\n1104:       annotations:\n1105:         checksum/config: {{ include (print $.Template.BasePath \"/configmaps/config.yaml\") . | sha256sum }}\n1106:         {{- with .Values.router.podAnnotations }}\n1107:         {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n1108:         {{- end }}\n1109:       labels:\n1110:         {{- include \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" . | nindent 8 }}\n1111:         app.kubernetes.io/component: router\n1112:         {{- with .Values.router.podLabels }}\n1113:         {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n1114:         {{- end }}\n1115:     spec:\n1116:       {{- with .Values.imagePullSecrets }}\n1117:       imagePullSecrets:\n1118:         {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n1119:       {{- end }}\n1120:       serviceAccountName: {{ include \"agentcube.router.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n1121:       securityContext:\n1122:         {{- toYaml .Values.router.securityContext | nindent 8 }}\n1123:       {{- with .Values.router.nodeSelector }}\n1124:       nodeSelector:\n1125:         {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n1126:       {{- end }}\n1127:       {{- with .Values.router.affinity }}\n1128:       affinity:\n1129:         {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n1130:       {{- end }}\n1131:       {{- with .Values.router.tolerations }}\n1132:       tolerations:\n1133:         {{- toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n1134:       {{- end }}\n1135:       {{- if .Values.priorityClassName }}\n1136:       priorityClassName: {{ .Values.priorityClassName }}\n1137:       {{- end }}\n1138:       containers:\n1139:       - name: router\n1140:         securityContext:\n1141:           {{- toYaml .Values.router.containerSecurityContext | nindent 10 }}\n1142:         image: \"{{ include \"agentcube.image\" (dict \"registry\" .Values.global.imageRegistry \"repository\" .Values.router.image.repository \"tag\" .Values.router.image.tag) }}\"\n1143:         imagePullPolicy: {{ .Values.router.image.pullPolicy }}\n1144:         args:\n1145:         - --leader-elect\n1146:         - --health-probe-bind-address=:8080\n1147:         - --metrics-bind-address=:9090\n1148:         ports:\n1149:         - name: http\n1150:           containerPort: 8080\n1151:           protocol: TCP\n1152:         - name: metrics\n1153:           containerPort: 9090\n1154:           protocol: TCP\n1155:         {{- with .Values.router.livenessProbe }}\n1156:         livenessProbe:\n1157:           {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n1158:         {{- end }}\n1159:         {{- with .Values.router.readinessProbe }}\n1160:         readinessProbe:\n1161:           {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n1162:         {{- end }}\n1163:         resources:\n1164:           {{- toYaml .Values.router.resources | nindent 10 }}\n1165:         {{- with .Values.router.env }}\n1166:         env:\n1167:           {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n1168:         {{- end }}\n1169:         {{- with .Values.router.envFrom }}\n1170:         envFrom:\n1171:           {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n1172:         {{- end }}\n1173:         {{- with .Values.router.extraVolumeMounts }}\n1174:         volumeMounts:\n1175:           {{- toYaml . | nindent 10 }}\n1176:         {{- end }}\n1177:       {{- with .Values.router.extraVolumes }}\n1178:       volumes:\n1179:         {{- toYaml . | nindent 6 }}\n1180:       {{- end }}\n1181: {{- end }}\n1182: ```\n1183: \n1184: ### Template: ServiceMonitor\n1185: \n1186: **File:** `templates/monitoring/servicemonitor.yaml`\n1187: \n1188: ```yaml\n1189: {{- if and .Values.monitoring.enabled .Values.monitoring.serviceMonitor.enabled }}\n1190: apiVersion: monitoring.coreos.com/v1\n1191: kind: ServiceMonitor\n1192: metadata:\n1193:   name: {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}\n1194:   namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n1195:   labels:\n1196:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n1197:     {{- with .Values.monitoring.serviceMonitor.labels }}\n1198:     {{- toYaml . | nindent 4 }}\n1199:     {{- end }}\n1200:   {{- with .Values.monitoring.serviceMonitor.annotations }}\n1201:   annotations:\n1202:     {{- toYaml . | nindent 4 }}\n1203:   {{- end }}\n1204: spec:\n1205:   selector:\n1206:     matchLabels:\n1207:       {{- include \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" . | nindent 6 }}\n1208:   namespaceSelector:\n1209:     matchNames:\n1210:       - {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n1211:   endpoints:\n1212:   - port: metrics\n1213:     interval: {{ .Values.monitoring.serviceMonitor.interval }}\n1214:     scrapeTimeout: {{ .Values.monitoring.serviceMonitor.scrapeTimeout }}\n1215:     path: /metrics\n1216:     {{- with .Values.monitoring.serviceMonitor.metricRelabelings }}\n1217:     metricRelabelings:\n1218:       {{- toYaml . | nindent 4 }}\n1219:     {{- end }}\n1220:     {{- with .Values.monitoring.serviceMonitor.relabelings }}\n1221:     relabelings:\n1222:       {{- toYaml . | nindent 4 }}\n1223:     {{- end }}\n1224: {{- end }}\n1225: ```\n1226: \n1227: ### Template: PodDisruptionBudget\n1228: \n1229: **File:** `templates/poddisruptionbudgets/controller-manager.yaml`\n1230: \n1231: ```yaml\n1232: {{- if and .Values.controllerManager.enabled .Values.controllerManager.podDisruptionBudget.enabled }}\n1233: apiVersion: policy/v1\n1234: kind: PodDisruptionBudget\n1235: metadata:\n1236:   name: {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}\n1237:   namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n1238:   labels:\n1239:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n1240:     app.kubernetes.io/component: controller-manager\n1241: spec:\n1242:   minAvailable: {{ .Values.controllerManager.podDisruptionBudget.minAvailable }}\n1243:   selector:\n1244:     matchLabels:\n1245:       {{- include \"agentcube.selectorLabels\" . | nindent 6 }}\n1246:       app.kubernetes.io/component: controller-manager\n1247: {{- end }}\n1248: ```\n1249: \n1250: ### Template: Ingress\n1251: \n1252: **File:** `templates/ingress.yaml`\n1253: \n1254: ```yaml\n1255: {{- if .Values.ingress.enabled }}\n1256: apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1\n1257: kind: Ingress\n1258: metadata:\n1259:   name: {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}\n1260:   namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n1261:   labels:\n1262:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n1263:   {{- with .Values.ingress.annotations }}\n1264:   annotations:\n1265:     {{- toYaml . | nindent 4 }}\n1266:   {{- end }}\n1267: spec:\n1268:   ingressClassName: {{ .Values.ingress.className }}\n1269:   {{- if .Values.ingress.tls }}\n1270:   tls:\n1271:     {{- range .Values.ingress.tls }}\n1272:     - hosts:\n1273:         {{- range .hosts }}\n1274:         - {{ . | quote }}\n1275:         {{- end }}\n1276:       secretName: {{ .secretName }}\n1277:     {{- end }}\n1278:   {{- end }}\n1279:   rules:\n1280:     {{- range .Values.ingress.hosts }}\n1281:     - host: {{ .host | quote }}\n1282:       http:\n1283:         paths:\n1284:           {{- range .paths }}\n1285:           - path: {{ .path }}\n1286:             pathType: {{ .pathType }}\n1287:             backend:\n1288:               service:\n1289:                 name: {{ .backend.service.name | default (printf \"%s-router\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" $)) }}\n1290:                 port:\n1291:                   number: {{ .backend.service.port.number | default 8080 }}\n1292:           {{- end }}\n1293:     {{- end }}\n1294: {{- end }}\n1295: ```\n1296: \n1297: ### Template: NetworkPolicy\n1298: \n1299: **File:** `templates/networkpolicies/networkpolicy.yaml`\n1300: \n1301: ```yaml\n1302: {{- if .Values.networkPolicies.enabled }}\n1303: apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1\n1304: kind: NetworkPolicy\n1305: metadata:\n1306:   name: {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}\n1307:   namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n1308:   labels:\n1309:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n1310: spec:\n1311:   podSelector: {}\n1312:   {{- if .Values.networkPolicies.defaultDeny }}\n1313:   policyTypes:\n1314:   - Ingress\n1315:   - Egress\n1316:   {{- end }}\n1317:   ingress:\n1318:   {{- range .Values.networkPolicies.rules.controllerManager.ingress }}\n1319:   - from:\n1320:     {{- range .from }}\n1321:     {{- toYaml . | nindent 6 }}\n1322:     {{- end }}\n1323:     ports:\n1324:     {{- range .ports }}\n1325:     - {{ toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n1326:     {{- end }}\n1327:   {{- end }}\n1328:   egress:\n1329:   {{- range .Values.networkPolicies.rules.controllerManager.egress }}\n1330:   - to:\n1331:     {{- range .to }}\n1332:     {{- toYaml . | nindent 6 }}\n1333:     {{- end }}\n1334:     ports:\n1335:     {{- range .ports }}\n1336:     - {{ toYaml . | nindent 8 }}\n1337:     {{- end }}\n1338:   {{- end }}\n1339: {{- end }}\n1340: ```\n1341: \n1342: ### Template: ConfigMap\n1343: \n1344: **File:** `templates/configmaps/config.yaml`\n1345: \n1346: ```yaml\n1347: {{- if .Values.configMaps.agentcubeConfig.create }}\n1348: apiVersion: v1\n1349: kind: ConfigMap\n1350: metadata:\n1351:   name: {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}-config\n1352:   namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n1353:   labels:\n1354:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n1355: data:\n1356:   {{- toYaml .Values.configMaps.agentcubeConfig.data | nindent 2 }}\n1357: {{- end }}\n1358: ```\n1359: \n1360: ### Template: Secret\n1361: \n1362: **File:** `templates/secrets/secret.yaml`\n1363: \n1364: ```yaml\n1365: {{- if .Values.secrets.create }}\n1366: apiVersion: v1\n1367: kind: Secret\n1368: metadata:\n1369:   name: {{ .Values.secrets.name | default (printf \"%s-secrets\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .)) }}\n1370:   namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n1371:   labels:\n1372:     {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n1373: type: Opaque\n1374: data:\n1375:   {{- range $key, $value := .Values.secrets.data }}\n1376:   {{ $key }}: {{ $value | b64enc }}\n1377:   {{- end }}\n1378: {{- end }}\n1379: ```\n1380: \n1381: ### Template: NOTES.txt\n1382: \n1383: **File:** `templates/NOTES.txt`\n1384: \n1385: ```yaml\n1386: Thank you for installing {{ .Chart.Name }}!\n1387: \n1388: Your release is named {{ .Release.Name }}.\n1389: \n1390: To learn more about the release, try:\n1391: \n1392:   $ helm status {{ .Release.Name }}\n1393:   $ helm get all {{ .Release.Name }}\n1394: \n1395: {{- if .Values.ingress.enabled }}\n1396: To access the AgentCube Router:\n1397: \n1398:   {{- range .Values.ingress.hosts }}\n1399:   http{{ if $.Values.ingress.tls }}s{{ end }}://{{ .host }}\n1400:   {{- end }}\n1401: \n1402: {{- else if contains \"NodePort\" .Values.router.service.type }}\n1403: \n1404: Get the Router URL by running these commands:\n1405: \n1406:   export NODE_PORT=$(kubectl get --namespace {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }} -o jsonpath=\"{.spec.ports[0].nodePort}\" services {{ printf \"%s-router\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }})\n1407:   export NODE_IP=$(kubectl get nodes --namespace {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }} -o jsonpath=\"{.items[0].status.addresses[0].address}\")\n1408: \n1409:   echo http://$NODE_IP:$NODE_PORT\n1410: \n1411: {{- else if contains \"LoadBalancer\" .Values.router.service.type }}\n1412: \n1413: Get the Router URL by running these commands:\n1414: \n1415:   NOTE: It may take a few minutes for the LoadBalancer IP to be available.\n1416:         You can watch the status by running 'kubectl get svc --namespace {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }} -w {{ printf \"%s-router\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }}'\n1417: \n1418:   export SERVICE_IP=$(kubectl get svc --namespace {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }} {{ printf \"%s-router\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }} -o jsonpath='{.status.loadBalancer.ingress[0].ip}')\n1419: \n1420:   echo http://$SERVICE_IP:{{ .Values.router.service.port }}\n1421: \n1422: {{- else if contains \"ClusterIP\" .Values.router.service.type }}\n1423: \n1424: Get the Router URL by running these commands:\n1425: \n1426:   export POD_NAME=$(kubectl get pods --namespace {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }} -l \"app.kubernetes.io/name={{ include \"agentcube.name\" . }},app.kubernetes.io/instance={{ .Release.Name }},app.kubernetes.io/component=router\" -o jsonpath=\"{.items[0].metadata.name}\")\n1427: \n1428:   kubectl port-forward --namespace {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }} $POD_NAME 8080:8080\n1429: \n1430:   echo \"Visit http://127.0.0.1:8080 to use the AgentCube Router\"\n1431: \n1432: {{- end }}\n1433: \n1434: {{- if .Values.monitoring.enabled }}\n1435: \n1436: Monitoring is enabled. ServiceMonitor {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }} has been created.\n1437: \n1438: To verify Prometheus is scraping metrics:\n1439: \n1440:   $ kubectl get servicemonitor {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }} -n {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n1441: \n1442: {{- end }}\n1443: \n1444: For more information, visit:\n1445:   https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n1446: ```\n1447: \n1448: ## Error Handling\n1449: \n1450: ### Helm Template Validation\n1451: \n1452: **Linting:**\n1453: ```bash\n1454: helm lint ./agentcube\n1455: ```\n1456: \n1457: **Template rendering validation:**\n1458: ```bash\n1459: helm template agentcube ./agentcube --debug\n1460: ```\n1461: \n1462: **Values validation:**\n1463: ```bash\n1464: helm show values ./agentcube > values.yaml\n1465: # Validate values.yaml manually or with schema validation tool\n1466: ```\n1467: \n1468: ### Common Template Errors\n1469: \n1470: | Error Type | Cause | Resolution |\n1471: |------------|-------|------------|\n1472: | `variable not defined` | Reference to undefined template variable | Ensure variable is defined in _helpers.tpl or passed as parameter |\n1473: | `invalid type for index` | Trying to index non-map/slice type | Check value type before indexing |\n1474: | `nil pointer dereference` | Accessing field of nil value | Use `with` or `if` to check for nil |\n1475: | `unexpected end` | Unclosed template block | Check for matching `{{-` and `}}` |\n1476: | `redefinition` | Duplicate template definition | Ensure each template has unique name |\n1477: | `unknown identifier` | Reference to unknown Go template function | Use available Helm template functions only |\n1478: \n1479: ### Values Validation Errors\n1480: \n1481: | Error | Condition | Message |\n1482: |-------|-----------|---------|\n1483: | Invalid port | Port outside 1-65535 range | \"Port must be between 1 and 65535\" |\n1484: | Invalid replica count | Replica count < 0 | \"Replica count must be non-negative\" |\n1485: | Missing required value | Required field not set | \"Required value 'X' not set\" |\n1486: | Invalid image tag | Empty image tag with tag required | \"Image tag cannot be empty\" |\n1487: | Invalid resource request | CPU/memory request > limit | \"Resource request cannot exceed limit\" |\n1488: \n1489: ### Installation/Upgrade Errors\n1490: \n1491: ```bash\n1492: # Error: CRD already exists with different schema\n1493: Solution: helm upgrade --install --force or manually delete CRD\n1494: \n1495: # Error: Namespace does not exist\n1496: Solution: kubectl create namespace <namespace>\n1497: \n1498: # Error: Image pull failure\n1499: Solution: Check imagePullSecrets and image registry access\n1500: \n1501: # Error: Insufficient resources\n1502: Solution: Adjust resource requests/limits in values.yaml\n1503: \n1504: # Error: RBAC permissions denied\n1505: Solution: Ensure cluster-admin role or create necessary RBAC\n1506: ```\n1507: \n1508: ### Rollback Strategy\n1509: \n1510: ```bash\n1511: # View revision history\n1512: helm history <release-name>\n1513: \n1514: # Rollback to previous version\n1515: helm rollback <release-name> <revision>\n1516: \n1517: # Rollback with specific values\n1518: helm rollback <release-name> <revision> --reuse-values\n1519: \n1520: # Rollback and reconfigure\n1521: helm rollback <release-name> <revision> -f values.yaml\n1522: ```\n1523: \n1524: ### Error Reporting\n1525: \n1526: **Custom error messages in templates:**\n1527: ```yaml\n1528: {{- if not .Values.controllerManager.enabled }}\n1529: {{- fail \"Controller Manager must be enabled for AgentCube to function\" }}\n1530: {{- end }}\n1531: \n1532: {{- if lt .Values.router.replicaCount 1 }}\n1533: {{- fail \"Router replica count must be at least 1\" }}\n1534: {{- end }}\n1535: \n1536: {{- if not (hasKey .Values.controllerManager.image \"tag\") }}\n1537: {{- fail \"Controller Manager image tag is required\" }}\n1538: {{- end }}\n1539: ```\n1540: \n1541: ## Testing Strategy\n1542: \n1543: ### Unit Tests\n1544: \n1545: **Template Testing:**\n1546: \n1547: ```yaml\n1548: # tests/controller-manager_test.yaml\n1549: suite: controller manager deployment test\n1550: templates:\n1551:   - templates/controller-manager/deployment.yaml\n1552: tests:\n1553:   - it: should render deployment\n1554:     asserts:\n1555:       - isKind:\n1556:           of: Deployment\n1557:       - equal:\n1558:           path: metadata.name\n1559:           value: agentcube\n1560:   - it: should set correct replicas\n1561:     asserts:\n1562:       - equal:\n1563:           path: spec.replicas\n1564:           value: 2\n1565:   - it: should set correct image\n1566:     asserts:\n1567:       - equal:\n1568:           path: spec.template.spec.containers[0].image\n1569:           value: agentcube/controller-manager:v1.0.0\n1570:   - it: should set correct resource limits\n1571:     asserts:\n1572:       - equal:\n1573:           path: spec.template.spec.containers[0].resources.limits.cpu\n1574:           value: 500m\n1575:       - equal:\n1576:           path: spec.template.spec.containers[0].resources.limits.memory\n1577:           value: 512Mi\n1578:   - it: should set security context\n1579:     asserts:\n1580:       - equal:\n1581:           path: spec.template.spec.securityContext.runAsNonRoot\n1582:           value: true\n1583:   - it: should disable deployment when disabled\n1584:     set:\n1585:       controllerManager.enabled: false\n1586:     asserts:\n1587:       - hasDocuments:\n1588:           count: 0\n1589: ```\n1590: \n1591: **Values Testing:**\n1592: \n1593: ```yaml\n1594: # tests/values_test.yaml\n1595: suite: values validation\n1596: tests:\n1597:   - it: should require valid replica count\n1598:     set:\n1599:       controllerManager.replicaCount: -1\n1600:     asserts:\n1601:       - failedTemplate:\n1602:           errorMessage: \"Replica count must be non-negative\"\n1603:   - it: should require valid port\n1604:     set:\n1605:       controllerManager.service.port: 70000\n1606:     asserts:\n1607:       - failedTemplate:\n1608:           errorMessage: \"Port must be between 1 and 65535\"\n1609: ```\n1610: \n1611: **Helper Template Testing:**\n1612: \n1613: ```yaml\n1614: # tests/helpers_test.yaml\n1615: suite: helper templates\n1616: templates:\n1617:   - templates/_helpers.tpl\n1618: tests:\n1619:   - it: should generate correct full name\n1620:     asserts:\n1621:       - matchRegex:\n1622:           path: agentcube.fullname\n1623:           pattern: \"^agentcube-.*\"\n1624:   - it: should generate correct labels\n1625:     asserts:\n1626:       - contains:\n1627:           path: agentcube.labels\n1628:           content: app.kubernetes.io/name\n1629:       - contains:\n1630:           path: agentcube.labels\n1631:           content: helm.sh/chart\n1632: ```\n1633: \n1634: ### Integration Tests\n1635: \n1636: **Installation Test:**\n1637: \n1638: ```bash\n1639: #!/bin/bash\n1640: # test/integration/install_test.sh\n1641: \n1642: set -e\n1643: \n1644: echo \"Testing Helm Chart Installation...\"\n1645: \n1646: # Create namespace\n1647: kubectl create namespace agentcube-test --dry-run=client -o yaml | kubectl apply -f -\n1648: \n1649: # Install chart\n1650: helm install agentcube-test ./agentcube \\\n1651:   --namespace agentcube-test \\\n1652:   --values values-test.yaml \\\n1653:   --wait --timeout 5m\n1654: \n1655: # Verify deployments\n1656: kubectl rollout status deployment/agentcube-test -n agentcube-test\n1657: kubectl rollout status deployment/agentcube-test-workload-manager -n agentcube-test\n1658: kubectl rollout status deployment/agentcube-test-router -n agentcube-test\n1659: \n1660: # Verify services\n1661: kubectl get svc -n agentcube-test\n1662: kubectl get endpoints -n agentcube-test\n1663: \n1664: # Verify pods are running\n1665: kubectl get pods -n agentcube-test -l app.kubernetes.io/name=agentcube\n1666: \n1667: echo \"Installation test passed!\"\n1668: ```\n1669: \n1670: **Upgrade Test:**\n1671: \n1672: ```bash\n1673: #!/bin/bash\n1674: # test/integration/upgrade_test.sh\n1675: \n1676: set -e\n1677: \n1678: echo \"Testing Helm Chart Upgrade...\"\n1679: \n1680: # Initial installation\n1681: helm install agentcube-upgrade ./agentcube \\\n1682:   --namespace agentcube-upgrade \\\n1683:   --values values-test.yaml \\\n1684:   --set controllerManager.replicaCount=2\n1685: \n1686: # Upgrade with new values\n1687: helm upgrade agentcube-upgrade ./agentcube \\\n1688:   --namespace agentcube-upgrade \\\n1689:   --values values-test.yaml \\\n1690:   --set controllerManager.replicaCount=3 \\\n1691:   --reuse-values\n1692: \n1693: # Verify upgrade\n1694: kubectl rollout status deployment/agentcube-upgrade -n agentcube-upgrade\n1695: \n1696: # Check replica count\n1697: REPLICAS=$(kubectl get deployment agentcube-upgrade -n agentcube-upgrade -o jsonpath='{.spec.replicas}')\n1698: if [ \"$REPLICAS\" != \"3\" ]; then\n1699:   echo \"Upgrade test failed: expected 3 replicas, got $REPLICAS\"\n1700:   exit 1\n1701: fi\n1702: \n1703: echo \"Upgrade test passed!\"\n1704: ```\n1705: \n1706: **Rollback Test:**\n1707: \n1708: ```bash\n1709: #!/bin/bash\n1710: # test/integration/rollback_test.sh\n1711: \n1712: set -e\n1713: \n1714: echo \"Testing Helm Chart Rollback...\"\n1715: \n1716: # Install and upgrade\n1717: helm install agentcube-rollback ./agentcube \\\n1718:   --namespace agentcube-rollback \\\n1719:   --values values-test.yaml \\\n1720:   --set controllerManager.replicaCount=2\n1721: \n1722: helm upgrade agentcube-rollback ./agentcube \\\n1723:   --namespace agentcube-rollback \\\n1724:   --values values-test.yaml \\\n1725:   --set controllerManager.replicaCount=3 \\\n1726:   --reuse-values\n1727: \n1728: # Rollback\n1729: helm rollback agentcube-rollback 0 -n agentcube-rollback\n1730: \n1731: # Verify rollback\n1732: REPLICAS=$(kubectl get deployment agentcube-rollback -n agentcube-rollback -o jsonpath='{.spec.replicas}')\n1733: if [ \"$REPLICAS\" != \"2\" ]; then\n1734:   echo \"Rollback test failed: expected 2 replicas, got $REPLICAS\"\n1735:   exit 1\n1736: fi\n1737: \n1738: echo \"Rollback test passed!\"\n1739: ```\n1740: \n1741: ### E2E Tests\n1742: \n1743: **Functional Test:**\n1744: \n1745: ```bash\n1746: #!/bin/bash\n1747: # test/e2e/functional_test.sh\n1748: \n1749: set -e\n1750: \n1751: echo \"Running E2E Functional Tests...\"\n1752: \n1753: # Install chart\n1754: helm install agentcube-e2e ./agentcube \\\n1755:   --namespace agentcube-e2e \\\n1756:   --values values-test.yaml \\\n1757:   --wait\n1758: \n1759: # Test CRD creation\n1760: kubectl apply -f ../config/samples/runtime_v1alpha1_agentruntime.yaml\n1761: \n1762: # Wait for resource reconciliation\n1763: sleep 10\n1764: \n1765: # Verify AgentRuntime status\n1766: STATUS=$(kubectl get agentruntime example-runtime -n default -o jsonpath='{.status.conditions[0].status}')\n1767: if [ \"$STATUS\" != \"True\" ]; then\n1768:   echo \"Functional test failed: AgentRuntime not ready\"\n1769:   exit 1\n1770: fi\n1771: \n1772: # Test endpoint connectivity\n1773: SERVICE_IP=$(kubectl get svc agentcube-e2e-router -n agentcube-e2e -o jsonpath='{.spec.clusterIP}')\n1774: curl -f http://$SERVICE_IP:8080/healthz || exit 1\n1775: \n1776: echo \"E2E Functional test passed!\"\n1777: ```\n1778: \n1779: **Environment Test:**\n1780: \n1781: ```bash\n1782: #!/bin/bash\n1783: # test/e2e/environment_test.sh\n1784: \n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 1-1784. Use offset=1785 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-030: Helm Chart 模板与 Values — Design\n\n## Overview\n\nHelm Chart for AgentCube platform provides a standardized, configurable, and reusable Kubernetes deployment solution. The chart encapsulates all necessary Kubernetes resources (CRDs, Deployments, Services, ConfigMaps, RBAC) and enables flexible configuration through Values files, simplifying deployment across multiple environments.\n\n**Module:** `manifests`  \n**Language:** YAML + Go Templates  \n**Source Root:** `manifests/charts/agentcube/`  \n**Size:** L\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Chart Structure\n\n```\nagentcube/\n├── Chart.yaml                          # Chart metadata\n├── values.yaml                         # Default configuration\n├── values-dev.yaml                     # Development environment overrides","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-030/design.md","time":{"start":1775882975702,"end":1775882975727}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882975737,"sessionID":"ses_285208642ffeRWhsZ7Dp5Y3CSj","part":{"id":"prt_d7adfb9b6001zK9SGauIwOQsA7","messageID":"msg_d7adf9e2b001h4Wq7DiJA69QDv","sessionID":"ses_285208642ffeRWhsZ7Dp5Y3CSj","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-6032d1d7c3224e5e98c88cfbcff1322b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This design document outlines the architecture and implementation approach for the AgentRuntimeClient, a Python SDK client that provides a high-level interface for managing agents and their runtime sessions. The AgentRuntimeClient enables users to invoke agent workloads through the Router service with proper session management.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Components\n10: \n11: 1. **AgentRuntimeClient** - Main client class for agent runtime interactions\n12: 2. **AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient** - Handles HTTP communication with the Router for agent invocations\n13: 3. **Session Management Layer** - Manages session ID lifecycle (bootstrap/reuse)\n14: 4. **HTTP Client Layer** - Connection pooling and request handling via requests.Session\n15: 5. **Error Handling Layer** - Centralized exception handling\n16: 6. **Logging Layer** - Structured logging for debugging\n17: \n18: ### Design Patterns\n19: \n20: - **Context Manager Pattern** - For proper resource cleanup (`__enter__`/`__exit__`)\n21: - **Repository Pattern** - For agent runtime invocation operations\n22: - **Factory Pattern** - For creating HTTP sessions\n23: \n24: ## Package Structure\n25: \n26: The AgentRuntimeClient is part of the `agentcube-sdk` Python package:\n27: \n28: | Path | Role |\n29: |------|------|\n30: | `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports |\n31: | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` (main public API) |\n32: | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` (HTTP layer) |\n33: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception classes |\n34: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` (connection pooling) |\n35: | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` |\n36: \n37: ## Public API\n38: \n39: ### AgentRuntimeClient\n40: \n41: ```python\n42: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n43:     def __init__(\n44:         self,\n45:         agent_name: str,\n46:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n47:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n48:         verbose: bool = False,\n49:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n50:         timeout: int = 120,\n51:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n52:     ): ...\n53: \n54:     def __enter__(self): ...\n55:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n56: \n57:     def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any: ...\n58: \n59:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n60: ```\n61: \n62: **Instance fields:**\n63: - `agent_name: str` - Name of the agent to invoke\n64: - `namespace: str` - Kubernetes namespace for the agent\n65: - `timeout: int` - Default read timeout in seconds (default: 120)\n66: - `connect_timeout: float` - Connection timeout in seconds (default: 5.0)\n67: - `logger: logging.Logger` - Logger instance\n68: - `router_url: str` - Base URL for the Router service\n69: - `session_id: Optional[str]` - Agent runtime session ID\n70: - `dp_client: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` - Data plane client\n71: \n72: ### Configuration\n73: \n74: | Component | Resolved settings |\n75: |-----------|-------------------|\n76: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `ROUTER_URL`; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0` |\n77: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Same timeout defaults; base URL constructed from router_url, namespace, agent_name |\n78: \n79: ## HTTP Client Contract — Data Plane\n80: \n81: ### Base URL Construction\n82: \n83: ```text\n84: base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n85: self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n86: ```\n87: \n88: ### Endpoints\n89: \n90: | Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n91: |--------|-----|---------|------|\n92: | `GET` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` | — |\n93: | `POST` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n94: \n95: ### Session Bootstrap\n96: \n97: When `session_id` is not provided in `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__`:\n98: \n99: ```python\n100: # GET the base invocation URL to bootstrap session ID from response header\n101: response = session.get(base_url)\n102: session_id = response.headers.get(\"x-agentcube-session-id\")\n103: if not session_id:\n104:     raise ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")\n105: ```\n106: \n107: ### Timeout Behavior\n108: \n109: - **Connect timeout**: `connect_timeout` (default: 5.0 seconds)\n110: - **Read timeout**: `timeout` (default: 120 seconds) or per-call override\n111: - Timeout tuple: `(connect_timeout, timeout)` on each request\n112: \n113: ## Session Lifecycle\n114: \n115: ### Context Manager\n116: \n117: ```python\n118: with AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\") as client:\n119:     result = client.invoke({\"query\": \"hello\"})\n120: ```\n121: \n122: On context exit:\n123: - `close()` is called\n124: - Underlying `requests.Session` is closed\n125: \n126: ### Session ID Management\n127: \n128: **Option 1: Bootstrap (default)**\n129: ```python\n130: client = AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"my-agent\")\n131: # Session ID is bootstrapped from Router on first use\n132: result = client.invoke(payload)\n133: ```\n134: \n135: **Option 2: Reuse existing session**\n136: ```python\n137: client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n138:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n139:     session_id=\"existing-session-id\"\n140: )\n141: # Skip bootstrap, use provided session ID\n142: result = client.invoke(payload)\n143: ```\n144: \n145: **Error handling:**\n146: - If `session_id` is falsy when `invoke` is called → `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n147: \n148: ## Error Handling\n149: \n150: ### Exception Hierarchy\n151: \n152: ```python\n153: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n154:     \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n155:     pass\n156: \n157: class CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n158:     def __init__(self, exit_code, stderr, command=None):\n159:         self.exit_code = exit_code\n160:         self.stderr = stderr\n161:         self.command = command\n162:         super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n163: \n164: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n165:     \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"\n166:     pass\n167: \n168: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n169:     \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n170:     pass\n171: ```\n172: \n173: ### Error Scenarios\n174: \n175: | Scenario | Exception |\n176: |----------|-----------|\n177: | Router URL not provided | `ValueError` |\n178: | Session ID header missing on bootstrap | `ValueError` |\n179: | Invoke called without session ID | `ValueError` |\n180: | Network errors | `requests.exceptions.*` |\n181: | Router returns 4xx/5xx | Handled by caller (SDK returns raw response) |\n182: \n183: ## Dependencies\n184: \n185: ```toml\n186: dependencies = [\n187:     \"requests\",\n188:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n189:     \"cryptography\",\n190: ]\n191: \n192: requires-python = \">=3.10\"\n193: ```\n194: \n195: ## HTTP Session Management\n196: \n197: ### Connection Pooling\n198: \n199: ```python\n200: def create_session(\n201:     pool_connections: int = 10,\n202:     pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n203: ) -> requests.Session:\n204:     \"\"\"Create a requests.Session with connection pooling.\"\"\"\n205: ```\n206: \n207: Mounts `HTTPAdapter` for both `http://` and `https://` schemes.\n208: \n209: ### Default Parameters\n210: \n211: - `pool_connections: 10`\n212: - `pool_maxsize: 10`\n213: - `timeout: 120` (read)\n214: - `connect_timeout: 5.0`\n215: \n216: ## Testing Strategy\n217: \n218: ### Unit Tests\n219: \n220: - Test session ID bootstrap logic\n221: - Test invoke method with mocked HTTP responses\n222: - Test error handling (missing session ID, missing header)\n223: - Test timeout behavior\n224: - Test context manager cleanup\n225: \n226: ### Integration Tests\n227: \n228: - Test against real Router service\n229: - Test end-to-end agent invocation workflow\n230: - Test session reuse scenarios\n231: \n232: ## Security Considerations\n233: \n234: 1. **Router Communication**: SDK does not set `Authorization` header on data plane (Router handles JWT)\n235: 2. **Input Validation**: Basic validation of required parameters\n236: 3. **Error Messages**: Avoid exposing sensitive information\n237: \n238: ## Logging\n239: \n240: Structured logging via `get_logger`:\n241: - `INFO` level by default\n242: - Can be overridden via `verbose` parameter\n243: - Logs session ID bootstrap, invoke requests, and errors\n244: \n245: ## Example Usage\n246: \n247: ### Basic invocation with session bootstrap\n248: \n249: ```python\n250: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n251: \n252: with AgentRuntimeClient(\n253:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n254:     namespace=\"default\",\n255:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n256: ) as client:\n257:     result = client.invoke({\"query\": \"What is the capital of France?\"})\n258:     print(result)\n259: ```\n260: \n261: ### Reuse existing session\n262: \n263: ```python\n264: from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n265: \n266: client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n267:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n268:     session_id=\"existing-session-id\",\n269:     router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n270: )\n271: \n272: try:\n273:     result = client.invoke({\"query\": \"Hello\"}, timeout=60.0)\n274: finally:\n275:     client.close()\n276: ```\n277: \n278: ### Custom timeout\n279: \n280: ```python\n281: with AgentRuntimeClient(\n282:     agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n283:     timeout=180,  # 3 minutes\n284:     connect_timeout=10.0\n285: ) as client:\n286:     result = client.invoke({\"query\": \"Long-running task\"})\n287: ```\n288: \n289: ## Future Enhancements\n290: \n291: 1. **Async API**: Provide asynchronous versions of methods using `httpx.AsyncClient`\n292: 2. **Retry Logic**: Configurable retry with exponential backoff for transient failures\n293: 3. **Streaming**: Support streaming responses for long-running agent invocations\n294: 4. **Metrics**: Track request latency and success rates\n295: 5. **Event System**: Provide event-based API for agent lifecycle events\n\n(End of file - total 295 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Design Document\n\n## Overview\n\nThis design document outlines the architecture and implementation approach for the AgentRuntimeClient, a Python SDK client that provides a high-level interface for managing agents and their runtime sessions. The AgentRuntimeClient enables users to invoke agent workloads through the Router service with proper session management.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n1. **AgentRuntimeClient** - Main client class for agent runtime interactions\n2. **AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient** - Handles HTTP communication with the Router for agent invocations\n3. **Session Management Layer** - Manages session ID lifecycle (bootstrap/reuse)\n4. **HTTP Client Layer** - Connection pooling and request handling via requests.Session\n5. **Error Handling Layer** - Centralized exception handling\n6. **Logging Layer** - Structured logging for debugging\n\n### Design Patterns\n\n- **Context Manager Pattern** - For proper resource cleanup (`__enter__`/`__exit__`)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-028/design.md","time":{"start":1775882975706,"end":1775882975734}}}}
