{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775882984451,"sessionID":"ses_285208642ffeRWhsZ7Dp5Y3CSj","part":{"id":"prt_d7adfdc01001X9JdbeMu25uXFU","messageID":"msg_d7adfba31001uwOHkiv7b7Ppls","sessionID":"ses_285208642ffeRWhsZ7Dp5Y3CSj","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883100673,"sessionID":"ses_285208642ffeRWhsZ7Dp5Y3CSj","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae1a194001yhdQQBXBdFF4td","messageID":"msg_d7adfba31001uwOHkiv7b7Ppls","sessionID":"ses_285208642ffeRWhsZ7Dp5Y3CSj","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-e58add744c4f4fadaea19cbf3f1a04a8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-032: Dockerfile 多阶段构建 — Design Document\n\n## Overview\n\nThis design document outlines the technical implementation of a multi-stage Dockerfile build strategy for the AgentCube project. The implementation uses three independent build stages to create optimized production images, significantly reducing image size, improving build efficiency, enhancing security, and providing flexible image variants for different use cases.\n\n**Module:** `docker`  \n**Language:** Dockerfile  \n**Source Root:** `/changes/AR-032/`  \n**Size:** S\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Multi-Stage Build Architecture\n\nThe implementation follows a three-stage build architecture:\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     Build Pipeline                          │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                              │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │           Stage 1: Builder                            │  │\n│  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n│  │  │ • golang:1.21-alpine base image               │  │  │\n│  │  │ • Install build tools (gcc, musl-dev)        │  │  │\n│  │  │ • Download Go dependencies (go.mod/go.sum)   │  │  │\n│  │  │ • Copy source code                           │  │  │\n│  │  │ • Compile agentd binary                      │  │  │\n│  │  │ • Install Python dependencies                 │  │  │\n│  │  │ • Prepare picod environment                   │  │  │\n│  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n│                           │                                  │\n│                           ▼                                  │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │           Stage 2: Verifier (Optional)                │  │\n│  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n│  │  │ • Inherit from builder                        │  │  │\n│  │  │ • Run Go unit tests                           │  │  │\n│  │  │ • Run Python unit tests                       │  │  │\n│  │  │ • Execute code quality checks                 │  │  │\n│  │  │ • Verify build artifacts                      │  │  │\n│  │  │ • Generate test reports                       │  │  │\n│  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n│                           │                                  │\n│                           ▼                                  │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │           Stage 3: Runtime                            │  │\n│  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n│  │  │ • alpine:3.19 minimal base image              │  │  │\n│  │  │ • Install runtime deps only (ca-certificates) │  │  │\n│  │  │ • Create non-privileged user (agentcube:1000) │  │  │\n│  │  │ • Copy compiled agentd binary                 │  │  │\n│  │  │ • Copy Python site-packages                  │  │  │\n│  │  │ • Copy picod source code                      │  │  │\n│  │  │ • Configure health check                      │  │  │\n│  │  │ • Set security context                        │  │  │\n│  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n│                                                              │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Image Variants\n\nThe implementation provides three image variants for different use cases:\n\n| Variant | Target Stage | Tag | Use Case |\n|---------|--------------|-----|----------|\n| Production | Runtime | `:latest`, `:vX.Y.Z` | Production deployments |\n| Development | Builder | `:dev` | Debugging and development |\n| Test | Verifier | `:test` | Running test suites |\n\n### Build Flow\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    A[Source Code] --> B[Builder Stage]\n    B --> C[Compile agentd]\n    B --> D[Install Python deps]\n    C --> E[Optional: Verifier Stage]\n    D --> E\n    E --> F[Run Tests]\n    F --> G[Runtime Stage]\n    G --> H[Copy artifacts]\n    H --> I[Configure security]\n    I --> J[Production Image]\n    \n    B -.-> K[Development Image]\n    E -.-> L[Test Image]\n```\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Dockerfile Structure\n\n```dockerfile\n# ============================================\n# Build Arguments\n# ============================================\nARG GO_VERSION=1.21\nARG ALPINE_VERSION=3.19\nARG BUILD_VERSION=dev\nARG BUILD_TIME\nARG GIT_COMMIT\n\n# ============================================\n# Stage 1: Builder\n# ============================================\nFROM golang:${GO_VERSION}-alpine AS builder\n\n# Build metadata\nARG BUILD_VERSION\nARG BUILD_TIME\nARG GIT_COMMIT\n\n# Install build tools\nRUN apk add --no-cache \\\n    python3 \\\n    py3-pip \\\n    gcc \\\n    musl-dev \\\n    git\n\n# Set working directory\nWORKDIR /build\n\n# Go dependency optimization - download first for caching\nCOPY go.mod go.sum ./\nRUN go mod download\n\n# Copy Go source code\nCOPY ./pkg ./pkg\nCOPY ./cmd ./cmd\n\n# Build agentd with embedded version info\nRUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux go build \\\n    -ldflags=\"-s -w -X main.Version=${BUILD_VERSION} -X main.BuildTime=${BUILD_TIME} -X main.GitCommit=${GIT_COMMIT}\" \\\n    -o agentd \\\n    ./cmd/agentd\n\n# Copy Python source and dependencies\nCOPY ./cmd/picod /build/picod\nCOPY requirements.txt ./\nRUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt\n\n# ============================================\n# Stage 2: Verifier (Optional)\n# ============================================\nFROM builder AS verifier\n\n# Run Go tests\nRUN go test ./... -v -coverprofile=coverage.out\n\n# Run Python tests\nRUN pytest /build/picod/tests -v\n\n# Generate test report\nRUN go tool cover -html=coverage.out -o coverage.html\n\n# ============================================\n# Stage 3: Runtime\n# ============================================\nFROM alpine:${ALPINE_VERSION} AS runtime\n\n# Build metadata\nARG BUILD_VERSION\nARG GIT_COMMIT\n\n# Labels for image metadata\nLABEL maintainer=\"agentcube@volcano.sh\" \\\n      version=\"${BUILD_VERSION}\" \\\n      git.commit=\"${GIT_COMMIT}\" \\\n      description=\"AgentCube Runtime Image\"\n\n# Install runtime dependencies only\nRUN apk add --no-cache \\\n    ca-certificates \\\n    python3 \\\n    py3-pip \\\n    tzdata \\\n    && update-ca-certificates\n\n# Create non-privileged user\nRUN addgroup -g 1000 agentcube && \\\n    adduser -D -u 1000 -G agentcube agentcube\n\n# Set working directory\nWORKDIR /app\n\n# Copy compiled binaries from builder\nCOPY --from=builder /build/agentd /app/agentd\n\n# Copy Python environment\nCOPY --from=builder /usr/local/lib/python3.11/site-packages /usr/local/lib/python3.11/site-packages\nCOPY --from=builder /build/picod /app/picod\n\n# Set ownership\nRUN chown -R agentcube:agentcube /app\n\n# Switch to non-privileged user\nUSER agentcube\n\n# Expose ports\nEXPOSE 8080 9090\n\n# Health check\nHEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=10s --start-period=5s --retries=3 \\\n    CMD agentd health || exit 1\n\n# Entry point\nENTRYPOINT [\"/app/agentd\"]\n```\n\n### Build Arguments Schema\n\n| Argument | Default | Description | Usage |\n|----------|---------|-------------|-------|\n| `GO_VERSION` | `1.21` | Go compiler version | Controls base Go image |\n| `ALPINE_VERSION` | `3.19` | Alpine Linux version | Controls base runtime image |\n| `BUILD_VERSION` | `dev` | Application version | Embedded in binary metadata |\n| `BUILD_TIME` | (auto) | Build timestamp | Embedded in binary metadata |\n| `GIT_COMMIT` | (auto) | Git commit hash | Embedded in binary metadata |\n\n### Environment Variables Schema\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `AGENTCUBE_ENV` | `production` | Runtime environment |\n| `AGENTCUBE_LOG_LEVEL` | `info` | Logging level |\n| `AGENTCUBE_LOG_FORMAT` | `json` | Log format (json/text) |\n| `AGENTCUBE_PORT` | `8080` | Service port |\n| `AGENTCUBE_METRICS_ENABLED` | `true` | Enable metrics endpoint |\n| `AGENTCUBE_METRICS_PORT` | `9090` | Metrics port |\n\n### .dockerignore Patterns\n\n```dockerignore\n# Git files\n.git\n.gitignore\n.gitattributes\n\n# Documentation\n*.md\ndocs/\n\n# Development files\n.vscode/\n.idea/\n*.swp\n*.swo\n\n# Build artifacts\ndist/\nbuild/\n*.exe\n*.dll\n*.dylib\n\n# Test files\n*_test.go\npytest.ini\n.coverage\n.coverage.*\n\n# CI/CD\n.github/\n.gitlab-ci.yml\n.travis.yml\n\n# IDE\n.vscode/\n.idea/\n\n# OS\n.DS_Store\nThumbs.db\n\n# Temporary files\ntmp/\ntemp/\n*.tmp\n\n# Docker files (except Dockerfile)\ndocker-compose*.yml\n*.dockerfile\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Build Commands\n\n#### Single Architecture Build\n\n```bash\n# Build production image\ndocker build \\\n  --build-arg GO_VERSION=1.21 \\\n  --build-arg BUILD_VERSION=v1.0.0 \\\n  --build-arg BUILD_TIME=$(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ) \\\n  --build-arg GIT_COMMIT=$(git rev-parse --short HEAD) \\\n  -t agentcube:latest \\\n  -t agentcube:v1.0.0 \\\n  .\n\n# Build development image\ndocker build \\\n  --target builder \\\n  -t agentcube:dev \\\n  .\n\n# Build test image\ndocker build \\\n  --target verifier \\\n  -t agentcube:test \\\n  .\n```\n\n#### Multi-Architecture Build\n\n```bash\n# Create and use buildx builder\ndocker buildx create --name agentcube-builder --use\n\n# Build and push multi-arch images\ndocker buildx build \\\n  --platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n  --build-arg GO_VERSION=1.21 \\\n  --build-arg BUILD_VERSION=v1.0.0 \\\n  --build-arg BUILD_TIME=$(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ) \\\n  --build-arg GIT_COMMIT=$(git rev-parse --short HEAD) \\\n  -t registry.example.com/agentcube:latest \\\n  -t registry.example.com/agentcube:v1.0.0 \\\n  --push \\\n  .\n\n# Build multi-arch images locally\ndocker buildx build \\\n  --platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n  -t agentcube:multiarch \\\n  --load \\\n  .\n```\n\n### Runtime API\n\n#### Container Entry Points\n\n| Stage | Entry Point | Default Command |\n|-------|-------------|-----------------|\n| Builder | `/bin/sh` | Interactive shell |\n| Verifier | `/bin/sh` | Test execution scripts |\n| Runtime | `/app/agentd` | Start agentd daemon |\n\n#### Health Check Endpoint\n\n```\nGET /healthz\nResponse: 200 OK (healthy) or 503 Service Unavailable (unhealthy)\n```\n\n#### Metrics Endpoint\n\n```\nGET /metrics\nResponse: Prometheus metrics format\n```\n\n### Build Output Schema\n\n#### Image Layer Information\n\n```bash\ndocker history agentcube:latest\n```\n\nOutput structure:\n```\nIMAGE           CREATED         CREATED BY                                      SIZE\n<runtime-id>    <timestamp>     /bin/sh -c #(nop) CMD [\"/app/agentd\"]          0B\n<runtime-id>    <timestamp>     /bin/sh -c #(nop) HEALTHCHECK...                0B\n<runtime-id>    <timestamp>     /bin/sh -c #(nop) EXPOSE 8080 9090              0B\n<runtime-id>    <timestamp>     /bin/sh -c #(nop) USER agentcube                0B\n<runtime-id>    <timestamp>     /bin/sh -c chown -R agentcube:agentcube /app    1.2MB\n<runtime-id>    <timestamp>     /bin/sh -c #(nop) COPY dir:... in /app/picod    5.5MB\n<runtime-id>    <timestamp>     /bin/sh -c #(nop) COPY dir:... in /usr/local   85MB\n<runtime-id>    <timestamp>     /bin/sh -c #(nop) COPY file:... in /app/agentd  15MB\n<runtime-id>    <timestamp>     /bin/sh -c apk add --no-cache ca-certificates... 12MB\n<runtime-id>    <timestamp>     /bin/sh -c addgroup -g 1000 agentcube && ...    1.5KB\n<runtime-id>    <timestamp>     /bin/sh -c #(nop) WORKDIR /app                   0B\n<runtime-id>    <timestamp>     <base-image-id>                                  7.5MB\n```\n\n#### Image Size Analysis\n\n```bash\ndocker images agentcube:latest --format \"{{.Size}}\"\n```\n\nExpected output:\n- **Production Image**: ~150-250 MB\n- **Builder Image**: ~800-1200 MB\n- **Verifier Image**: ~850-1250 MB\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Build Time Errors\n\n#### Dockerfile Syntax Errors\n\n**Detection:**\n```bash\ndocker build --check .\n```\n\n**Common Errors:**\n\n| Error | Cause | Resolution |\n|-------|-------|------------|\n| `unknown instruction` | Invalid Dockerfile syntax | Verify Dockerfile syntax and Docker version |\n| `failed to compute cache key` | Missing file or incorrect path | Check COPY paths and file existence |\n| `no such file or directory` | Source file not found | Verify file paths and .dockerignore |\n| `failed to solve` | Dependency unavailable | Check network connectivity and base image availability |\n\n#### Build Failures\n\n**Go Compilation Errors:**\n```\nStep X/Y : RUN go build -o agentd ./cmd/agentd\n ---> Running in <container-id>\n# github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/cmd/agentd\n./main.go:XX:YY: undefined: Foo\nerror building image\n```\n\n**Resolution:**\n1. Check Go code for compilation errors\n2. Verify Go version compatibility\n3. Ensure all dependencies are in go.mod\n4. Check for platform-specific code issues\n\n**Python Dependency Errors:**\n```\nStep X/Y : RUN pip install -r requirements.txt\n ---> Running in <container-id>\nERROR: Could not find a version that satisfies the requirement Foo\nerror building image\n```\n\n**Resolution:**\n1. Verify requirements.txt syntax\n2. Check dependency availability in PyPI\n3. Ensure Python version compatibility\n4. Use pinned versions for reproducibility\n\n### Runtime Errors\n\n#### Container Startup Failures\n\n**Binary Execution Errors:**\n```\nstandard_init_linux.go:228: exec user process caused: no such file or directory\n```\n\n**Resolution:**\n1. Verify binary was successfully copied from builder stage\n2. Check binary architecture compatibility\n3. Ensure proper execute permissions\n4. Verify dynamic library dependencies\n\n**Permission Errors:**\n```\npermission denied: trying to connect to the Docker daemon socket\n```\n\n**Resolution:**\n1. Verify non-privileged user configuration\n2. Check file ownership and permissions\n3. Review security context settings\n4. Ensure proper user/group IDs\n\n#### Health Check Failures\n\n**Detection:**\n```bash\ndocker inspect --format='{{.State.Health.Status}}' <container-id>\n```\n\n**Common Causes:**\n- Port not exposed or bound\n- Application not starting properly\n- Network configuration issues\n- Insufficient resources\n\n**Resolution:**\n1. Check application logs: `docker logs <container-id>`\n2. Verify port exposure and binding\n3. Review resource limits\n4. Test health endpoint manually\n\n### Validation Scripts\n\n#### Build Validation Script\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# scripts/validate-build.sh\n\nset -e\n\necho \"Validating Dockerfile...\"\n\n# Check syntax\necho \"Checking Dockerfile syntax...\"\ndocker build --check . || exit 1\n\n# Check base images\necho \"Verifying base images...\"\ndocker pull golang:1.21-alpine\ndocker pull alpine:3.19\n\n# Build all targets\necho \"Building all targets...\"\ndocker build --target builder -t agentcube:dev .\ndocker build --target verifier -t agentcube:test .\ndocker build -t agentcube:latest .\n\n# Verify image sizes\necho \"Checking image sizes...\"\nDEV_SIZE=$(docker images agentcube:dev --format \"{{.Size}}\")\nTEST_SIZE=$(docker images agentcube:test --format \"{{.Size}}\"))\nPROD_SIZE=$(docker images agentcube:latest --format \"{{.Size}}\")\n\necho \"Development image size: $DEV_SIZE\"\necho \"Test image size: $TEST_SIZE\"\necho \"Production image size: $PROD_SIZE\"\n\n# Check image layers\necho \"Inspecting image layers...\"\ndocker history agentcube:latest\n\necho \"Build validation completed successfully!\"\n```\n\n#### Runtime Validation Script\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# scripts/validate-runtime.sh\n\nset -e\n\necho \"Validating runtime container...\"\n\n# Run container\nCONTAINER_ID=$(docker run -d --name agentcube-test agentcube:latest)\n\n# Wait for startup\nsleep 10\n\n# Check container status\nSTATUS=$(docker inspect --format='{{.State.Status}}' $CONTAINER_ID)\necho \"Container status: $STATUS\"\n\n# Check health status\nHEALTH=$(docker inspect --format='{{.State.Health.Status}}' $CONTAINER_ID)\necho \"Health status: $HEALTH\"\n\n# Check logs\necho \"Container logs:\"\ndocker logs $CONTAINER_ID\n\n# Test health endpoint\necho \"Testing health endpoint...\"\ndocker exec $CONTAINER_ID wget -qO- http://localhost:8080/healthz\n\n# Cleanup\ndocker stop $CONTAINER_ID\ndocker rm $CONTAINER_ID\n\necho \"Runtime validation completed successfully!\"\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n#### Dockerfile Syntax Validation\n\n```bash\n# Use Hadolint for best practices checking\ndocker run --rm -i hadolint/hadolint hadolint --ignore DL3008 --ignore DL3018 < Dockerfile\n```\n\n#### Build Script Tests\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# tests/test-build-scripts.sh\n\n# Test 1: Verify build arguments\ntest_build_arguments() {\n    docker build \\\n      --build-arg GO_VERSION=1.21 \\\n      --build-arg BUILD_VERSION=test \\\n      -t test:args \\\n      .\n    \n    VERSION=$(docker run test:args /app/agentd version | jq -r '.version')\n    [ \"$VERSION\" = \"test\" ] || exit 1\n}\n\n# Test 2: Verify non-root user\ntest_non_root_user() {\n    USER=$(docker run --rm agentcube:latest whoami)\n    [ \"$USER\" = \"agentcube\" ] || exit 1\n}\n\n# Test 3: Verify binary execution\ntest_binary_execution() {\n    docker run --rm agentcube:latest /app/agentd version\n}\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n#### Build Integration Tests\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# tests/integration/build-integration.sh\n\nset -e\n\necho \"Running build integration tests...\"\n\n# Test 1: Full build pipeline\necho \"Test 1: Full build pipeline\"\ndocker build -t agentcube:integration-test .\n\n# Test 2: Multi-stage target selection\necho \"Test 2: Multi-stage target selection\"\ndocker build --target builder -t agentcube:builder-integration .\ndocker build --target verifier -t agentcube:verifier-integration .\n\n# Test 3: Layer caching\necho \"Test 3: Layer caching\"\nTIME1=$(time docker build -t agentcube:cache-test1 . 2>&1 | grep real)\nTIME2=$(time docker build -t agentcube:cache-test2 . 2>&1 | grep real)\necho \"First build: $TIME1\"\necho \"Cached build: $TIME2\"\n\n# Test 4: Multi-architecture build\necho \"Test 4: Multi-architecture build\"\ndocker buildx create --use\ndocker buildx build \\\n  --platform linux/amd64 \\\n  -t agentcube:amd64-test \\\n  --load \\\n  .\ndocker buildx build \\\n  --platform linux/arm64 \\\n  -t agentcube:arm64-test \\\n  --load \\\n  .\n\necho \"Build integration tests passed!\"\n```\n\n#### Runtime Integration Tests\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# tests/integration/runtime-integration.sh\n\nset -e\n\necho \"Running runtime integration tests...\"\n\n# Test 1: Container startup\necho \"Test 1: Container startup\"\nCONTAINER_ID=$(docker run -d agentcube:latest)\nsleep 10\nSTATUS=$(docker inspect --format='{{.State.Status}}' $CONTAINER_ID)\n[ \"$STATUS\" = \"running\" ] || exit 1\ndocker stop $CONTAINER_ID\n\n# Test 2: Health check\necho \"Test 2: Health check\"\nCONTAINER_ID=$(docker run -d agentcube:latest)\nsleep 15\nHEALTH=$(docker inspect --format='{{.State.Health.Status}}' $CONTAINER_ID)\n[ \"$HEALTH\" = \"healthy\" ] || exit 1\ndocker stop $CONTAINER_ID\n\n# Test 3: Port exposure\necho \"Test 3: Port exposure\"\nCONTAINER_ID=$(docker run -d -p 8080:8080 agentcube:latest)\nsleep 10\ncurl -f http://localhost:8080/healthz || exit 1\ndocker stop $CONTAINER_ID\n\n# Test 4: Resource constraints\necho \"Test 4: Resource constraints\"\nCONTAINER_ID=$(docker run -d --memory=\"512m\" --cpus=\"1.0\" agentcube:latest)\nsleep 10\nSTATUS=$(docker inspect --format='{{.State.Status}}' $CONTAINER_ID)\n[ \"$STATUS\" = \"running\" ] || exit 1\ndocker stop $CONTAINER_ID\n\necho \"Runtime integration tests passed!\"\n```\n\n### Performance Tests\n\n#### Build Performance Tests\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# tests/performance/build-performance.sh\n\necho \"Running build performance tests...\"\n\n# Test 1: Cold build time\necho \"Test 1: Cold build time\"\ndocker builder prune -af\nSTART=$(date +%s)\ndocker build -t agentcube:perf-cold .\nEND=$(date +%s)\necho \"Cold build time: $((END - START)) seconds\"\n\n# Test 2: Warm build time (with cache)\necho \"Test 2: Warm build time\"\nSTART=$(date +%s)\ndocker build -t agentcube:perf-warm .\nEND=$(date +%s)\necho \"Warm build time: $((END - START)) seconds\"\n\n# Test 3: Image size analysis\necho \"Test 3: Image size analysis\"\ndocker images agentcube:latest --format \"table {{.Repository}}\\t{{.Tag}}\\t{{.Size}}\"\ndocker history agentcube:latest\n\n# Test 4: Layer cache efficiency\necho \"Test 4: Layer cache efficiency\"\ndocker build --progress=plain -t agentcube:perf-cache . 2>&1 | grep -i \"cache\"\n\necho \"Build performance tests completed!\"\n```\n\n#### Runtime Performance Tests\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# tests/performance/runtime-performance.sh\n\necho \"Running runtime performance tests...\"\n\n# Test 1: Startup time\necho \"Test 1: Startup time\"\nSTART=$(date +%s%N)\nCONTAINER_ID=$(docker run -d agentcube:latest)\ndocker logs --follow $CONTAINER_ID &\nLOG_PID=$!\nwhile ! docker exec $CONTAINER_ID wget -qO- http://localhost:8080/healthz > /dev/null 2>&1; do\n    sleep 0.1\ndone\nEND=$(date +%s%N)\nkill $LOG_PID 2>/dev/null\nSTARTUP_TIME=$(( (END - START) / 1000000 ))\necho \"Startup time: ${STARTUP_TIME}ms\"\ndocker stop $CONTAINER_ID\n\n# Test 2: Memory usage\necho \"Test 2: Memory usage\"\nCONTAINER_ID=$(docker run -d agentcube:latest)\nsleep 10\nMEMORY=$(docker stats --no-stream --format \"{{.MemUsage}}\" $CONTAINER_ID)\necho \"Memory usage: $MEMORY\"\ndocker stop $CONTAINER_ID\n\n# Test 3: CPU usage\necho \"Test 3: CPU usage\"\nCONTAINER_ID=$(docker run -d agentcube:latest)\nsleep 10\nCPU=$(docker stats --no-stream --format \"{{.CPUPerc}}\" $CONTAINER_ID)\necho \"CPU usage: $CPU\"\ndocker stop $CONTAINER_ID\n\necho \"Runtime performance tests completed!\"\n```\n\n### Security Tests\n\n#### Vulnerability Scanning\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# tests/security/vulnerability-scan.sh\n\necho \"Running security vulnerability scans...\"\n\n# Test 1: Trivy scan\necho \"Test 1: Trivy scan\"\ndocker run --rm -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock \\\n  aquasec/trivy image \\\n  --severity HIGH,CRITICAL \\\n  --exit-code 1 \\\n  agentcube:latest\n\n# Test 2: Docker Scout scan\necho \"Test 2: Docker Scout scan\"\ndocker scout cves agentcube:latest\n\n# Test 3: Non-root user verification\necho \"Test 3: Non-root user verification\"\nUSER=$(docker run --rm agentcube:latest whoami)\n[ \"$USER\" != \"root\" ] || { echo \"ERROR: Container running as root\"; exit 1; }\n\n# Test 4: Sensitive data check\necho \"Test 4: Sensitive data check\"\ndocker history agentcube:latest | grep -i \"password\\|secret\\|key\" && \\\n  { echo \"ERROR: Potential sensitive data found\"; exit 1; }\n\necho \"Security tests passed!\"\n```\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n### Image Security\n\n1. **Base Image Selection**\n   - Use official images from Docker Hub\n   - Pin specific versions (e.g., `alpine:3.19` not `alpine:latest`)\n   - Regularly update base images\n   - Monitor security advisories\n\n2. **Minimal Attack Surface**\n   - Remove build tools and compilers from runtime image\n   - Use minimal base image (Alpine)\n   - Include only necessary runtime dependencies\n   - Avoid unnecessary packages\n\n3. **Non-Privileged Execution**\n   - Run as non-root user (UID 1000)\n   - Use minimal capabilities\n   - Implement read-only root filesystem (optional)\n   - Drop all Linux capabilities\n\n### Build Security\n\n1. **Secrets Management**\n   - Never embed secrets in Dockerfile\n   - Use `.dockerignore` to exclude sensitive files\n   - Pass secrets at runtime via environment variables or secrets management\n   - Use multi-stage builds to exclude build-time secrets\n\n2. **Dependency Security**\n   - Pin specific dependency versions\n   - Regularly update dependencies\n   - Scan dependencies for vulnerabilities\n   - Use signed packages when available\n\n3. **Build Context**\n   - Minimize build context with `.dockerignore`\n   - Exclude unnecessary files and directories\n   - Separate source from build artifacts\n   - Use build arguments for configuration\n\n### Runtime Security\n\n1. **Container Security Context**\n   ```dockerfile\n   USER agentcube\n   ```\n   - Run as non-privileged user\n   - Use read-only root filesystem (optional)\n   - Drop Linux capabilities\n   - Configure seccomp profiles\n\n2. **Network Security**\n   - Expose only necessary ports\n   - Use network policies\n   - Implement TLS for external communication\n   - Limit container network access\n\n3. **Resource Limits**\n   - Set CPU and memory limits\n   - Implement resource quotas\n   - Monitor resource usage\n   - Prevent resource exhaustion\n\n### Security Scanning\n\n```bash\n# Trivy vulnerability scan\ndocker run --rm -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock \\\n  aquasec/trivy image \\\n  --severity HIGH,CRITICAL \\\n  agentcube:latest\n\n# Docker Scout CVEs\ndocker scout cves agentcube:latest\n\n# Hadolint best practices\ndocker run --rm -i hadolint/hadolint hadolint < Dockerfile\n```\n\n## Performance Optimization\n\n### Build Optimization\n\n1. **Layer Caching Strategy**\n   - Order instructions from least to most frequently changing\n   - Copy dependency files before source code\n   - Use build arguments for version control\n   - Separate dependency installation from application copy\n\n2. **Multi-Stage Optimization**\n   - Minimize artifact transfer between stages\n   - Use `.dockerignore` to reduce build context\n   - Combine related commands in single RUN instruction\n   - Clean up temporary files in each stage\n\n3. **Build Parallelization**\n   ```bash\n   # Use BuildKit for parallel builds\n   DOCKER_BUILDKIT=1 docker build -t agentcube:latest .\n   ```\n\n### Runtime Optimization\n\n1. **Image Size Reduction**\n   - Use Alpine base image (~5MB)\n   - Remove package manager caches\n   - Use `--no-cache-dir` for pip\n   - Strip debug symbols from binaries\n   - Compress assets\n\n2. **Startup Time Optimization**\n   - Minimize entrypoint script complexity\n   - Use compiled binaries instead of interpreters\n   - Pre-initialize common resources\n   - Implement lazy loading\n\n3. **Memory Optimization**\n   - Use minimal runtime dependencies\n   - Implement connection pooling\n   - Optimize garbage collection settings\n   - Monitor memory usage patterns\n\n## Monitoring and Metrics\n\n### Build Metrics\n\n| Metric | Description | Target |\n|--------|-------------|--------|\n| Build Time | Time to complete build | < 5 minutes (cached) |\n| Image Size | Final image size | < 250 MB |\n| Layer Count | Number of layers | < 15 |\n| Cache Hit Rate | Percentage of cached layers | > 70% |\n\n### Runtime Metrics\n\n| Metric | Description | Target |\n|--------|-------------|--------|\n| Startup Time | Time to become healthy | < 10 seconds |\n| Memory Usage | steady-state memory | < 200 MB |\n| CPU Usage | steady-state CPU | < 10% |\n| Health Check Response | Health endpoint latency | < 100ms |\n\n### Metrics Collection\n\n```dockerfile\n# Expose metrics endpoint\nEXPOSE 9090\n\n# Metrics configuration\nENV AGENTCUBE_METRICS_ENABLED=true\nENV AGENTCUBE_METRICS_PORT=9090\n```\n\nAccess metrics:\n```\ncurl http://localhost:9090/metrics\n```\n\n## Implementation Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Foundation\n- [ ] Create Dockerfile structure\n- [ ] Define build arguments\n- [ ] Configure .dockerignore\n- [ ] Set up base images\n\n### Phase 2: Builder Stage\n- [ ] Install build tools\n- [ ] Configure Go environment\n- [ ] Implement Go dependency caching\n- [ ] Compile agentd binary\n- [ ] Configure Python environment\n- [ ] Install Python dependencies\n\n### Phase 3: Verifier Stage\n- [ ] Implement test execution\n- [ ] Configure code quality checks\n- [ ] Set up test reporting\n- [ ] Validate build artifacts\n\n### Phase 4: Runtime Stage\n- [ ] Configure Alpine base\n- [ ] Install runtime dependencies\n- [ ] Create non-privileged user\n- [ ] Copy build artifacts\n- [ ] Set up health checks\n- [ ] Configure security context\n\n### Phase 5: Build Scripts\n- [ ] Create build script\n- [ ] Create multi-architecture build script\n- [ ] Create validation scripts\n- [ ] Create test scripts\n\n### Phase 6: Documentation\n- [ ] Write Dockerfile comments\n- [ ] Create build guide\n- [ ] Create usage guide\n- [ ] Document troubleshooting steps\n\n### Phase 7: Testing\n- [ ] Implement unit tests\n- [ ] Implement integration tests\n- [ ] Implement performance tests\n- [ ] Implement security tests\n\n## References\n\n- [Docker Multi-stage Builds](https://docs.docker.com/build/building/multi-stage/)\n- [Docker Best Practices](https://docs.docker.com/develop/dev-best-practices/)\n- [Alpine Linux](https://alpinelinux.org/)\n- [Docker Buildx](https://docs.docker.com/buildx/working-with-buildx/)\n- [Hadolint](https://github.com/hadolint/hadolint)\n- [Trivy](https://github.com/aquasecurity/trivy)\n- [Docker Scout](https://docs.docker.com/scout/)\n- [AgentCube Project](../README.md)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_2